RESIDENTS of Manguzi in northern KZN have threatened to continue the town’s shutdown if government continues to fail them. The residents claimed that government had not done much to fight escalating crime in their area, which is close to the Kosi Bay border post that separates South Africa from Mozambique.The town has been brought to a standstill since Monday.if(typeof za24_DisplayAd != "undefined") za24_DisplayAd("300x250","2");var viewReq = new Array();function vu(u) {var i=new Image();i.src=u.replace("&amp;","&");viewReq.push(i);}vu("https://securepubads.g.doubleclick.net/pcs/view?xai\x3dAKAOjssb-1lcoHdwfZoIKkyLqS3UQhjZW4DAlymHa86cT8bnCH8UnyqNCJ_LEl1fB_hqyqBMh3RcmodPY54PAbUj1gycTZ76vHoVqpMhIKTSLcxoRBbCmeUk_fOAL0kPPEWd9EcrjJoRCK9TLhripAXOVuJ8QpUC7tlRlYrM0OCS2fqlEQc0cPNXMwfWaTmGBfGw_c8XTuWXu7Hb7N8U0BD4rXhsPXwxGZA5tCDQyqZOrKMN2d4rvcyPEqdmJIJKO2Xng3ZqDCRa5jci87UhgK3yTY3HEY7ENwo\x26sig\x3dCg0ArKJSzMpVVA7y4PnbEAE\x26urlfix\x3d1\x26adurl\x3d")

   
